1. *Svidelo* mu se kako je napisano pismo. (He liked how the letter was written.)
2. Njima se nije *svidelo* to što su morali da čekaju. (They didn't like that they had to wait.)
3. Da li ti se *svidelo* predstavljanje? (Did you like the presentation?)
4. *Svidelo* bi mi se da malo duže ostanem. (I would like to stay a little longer.)
5. Nikada mi se nije *svidelo* da čitam tu knjigu. (I never liked to read that book.)
6. *Svidelo* joj se njegovo ponašanje tokom večere. (She liked his behavior during dinner.)
7. Kolektivu se nije *svidelo* što je direktor doneo tu odluku. (The team didn't like that the director made that decision.)
8. *Svidelo* bi mi se da posetimo taj grad. (I would like to visit that city.)
9. Njemu se nije *svidelo* kako je ocenjen na ispitu. (He didn't like how he was graded on the exam.)
10. *Svidelo* bi joj se da ode na odmor na planinu. (She would like to go on a mountain vacation.)

(Note: The word "svidelo" is a past tense form of the verb "svideti se", which means "to like". In these examples, it is used in different forms and positions, such as past tense, conditional tense, and reflexive form.)